The paper proposes a novel deep architecture for knowledge graph embedding that utilizes both structural and textual information of entities. This involves the use of neural models to encode valuable information from text descriptions of entities, as well as a gating mechanism to integrate representations of structure and text into a unified architecture. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language), which are both concerned with natural language processing and machine learning. The paper also involves the use of neural models, which suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with knowledge graphs, which are a type of database, suggesting that cs.DB (Databases) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of information retrieval techniques, which suggests that cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible sub-category.
